Package: cptkirk
Title: Warp-Speed Remote GDAL Warping of Cloud-Optimised GeoTIFFs
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Hugh", "Graham", , "hugh@belian.earth", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A remote, overview-aware gdalwarp. cptkirk works out which source
    pixels a requested warp will touch, streams only those tiles over the
    Rust 'async-tiff' reader (with high remote-read saturation, at the
    appropriate overview level), stages them as an in-memory GDAL source, then
    hands the actual reprojection and resampling to GDAL via 'gdalraster',
    following the gdalwarp argument interface.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
